The State Department has appointed Ambassador David Satterfield as the U.S. Special Envoy for Middle East Humanitarian Issues. He will be responsible for ensuring life-saving assistance reaches vulnerable people in the Middle East. Ambassador Satterfield's diplomatic experience and extensive work in challenging conflicts will play a crucial role in addressing humanitarian issues in the region, which is a top priority for President Biden. This includes efforts to provide urgent humanitarian aid to the Palestinian people, particularly in Gaza, in collaboration with the U.N., Egypt, Jordan, Israel, and other regional stakeholders. The State Department expresses gratitude to Ambassador Satterfield for accepting this new role.